description:
Munich Air Disaster



Aired on 12/29/2011, Narrated by Jonathan Aris



On 6 February 1958, British European Airways Flight 609, an Airspeed Ambassador, carrying members of the famed Manchester United association football team, club officials and journalists, crashes into a house about 300 meters from the end of the runway in Munich after it fails to become airborne, killing 23 of the 44 people on board.
